17/01/2003
BELGRADE, Yugoslavia -- The commission on drafting the constitution of the future Yugoslav federation finally endorsed the text of the law on implementing the charter Thursday (16 January). 
Of the 27-member panel, 19 supported it and eight opposed it. 
Dragoljub Micunovic, a commission member and Yugoslav Parliament chairman, noted that a few minor technical details remain before the document is sent to the parliaments of Serbia and Montenegro. 
(BBC, FoNet, B92, Tanjug - 16/01/03)
